cs.£9/20/2014: Any time you have priority, you may turn the face-down creature face up by revealing what its morph cost is and paying that cost. This is a special action. It doesn’t use the stack and can’t be responded to. Only a face-down permanent can be turned face up this way; a face-down spell cannot.£9/20/2014: Because the permanent is on the battlefield both before and after it’s turned face up, turning a permanent face up doesn’t cause any enters-the-battlefield abilities to trigger.£9/20/2014: A permanent that turns face up or face down changes characteristics but is otherwise the same permanent. Spells and abilities that were targeting that permanent, as well as Auras and Equipment that were attached to the permanent, aren’t affected.£9/20/2014: At any time, you can look at a face-down spell or permanent you control. You can’t look at face-down spells or permanents you don’t control unless an effect instructs you to do so.£9/20/2014: You must ensure that your face-down spells and permanents can easily be differentiated from each other. You’re not allowed to mix up the cards that represent them on the battlefield in order to confuse other players. The order they entered the battlefield should remain clear. Common methods for doing this include using markers or dice, or simply placing them in order on the battlefield.£9/20/2014: If a face-down permanent leaves the battlefield, you must reveal it. You must also reveal all face-down spells and permanents you control if you leave the game or if the game ends.','R',NULL,'0.1','0.68','5.28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'R','烬云凤凰','燼雲鳳凰','Phénix des nuées cendreuses','Aschewolkenphoenix','Fenice della Nube Cinerea','灰雲のフェニックス','Fênix Nuvem-de-cinzas','Феникс Пепельного Облака','Fénix nubecinéreo','재구름 불사조','生物～凤凰','生物～鳳凰','Créature : phénix','Kreatur — Phoenix','Creatura — Fenice','クリーチャー ― フェニックス','Criatura — Fênix','Существо — Феникс','Criatura — Fénix','생물 — 불사조','飞行£当烬云凤凰死去时，将它牌面朝下地移回战场。£变身{4}{R}{R}（你可牌面朝下地施放此牌并支付{3}，将